<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-35-0965 </DOCNO><TEXT>The goal of moving from an offense-dominated to a defense-dominated internationalstrategic scene is desirable and feasible, and can best be achieved incooperation with the U.S.S.R. Such a shared goal implies that deployingstrategic defenses is clearly subordinate to the more encompassing matterof reducing ballistic missiles to zero or near zero. In addition to seekingSoviet cooperation, the U.S. should continue to discuss the pros andcons of such a direction with its allies, continue to conduct the strategicdefense initiative (SDI) technology program aimed at an earth-based defensewith passive defense, and continue to adhere to the 1972 ABM treaty.</TEXT></DOC>